Description: 
Stephen Grey and Dan Edge explore the reasoning 
behind the policy adopted by American special forces and 
troops as they seek to kill or capture Taliban and al-
Qaeda fighters, a campaign culminating in the shooting of 
Osama bin Laden in May 2011. The documentary, filmed 
over six months, examines evidence of the strategy's 
impact and cost, and features input from key military 
figures on both sides, who offer their perspective on the 
ongoing operation in Afghanistan.
